This paper proposes a congestion control protocol for wireless networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The protocol involves marking packets with "accelerate" or "brake" to guide senders towards a desired target rate, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and potentially cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also evaluates the protocol's performance using trace-driven emulation, which involves computer communications (cs.COMM) and potentially computer architecture (cs.AR).
